HEADWORD: Anemosis
<hw>An`e*mo"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ wind.]</ety> <def>A condition in the wood of some trees in which the
rings are separated, as some suppose, by the action of high winds upon
the trunk; wind shake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

